    "RQ1 was investigated through a quantitative analysis of article and citation counts over the years.",
    "To capture non-linear trends in the annual paper output, a polynomial modeling approach was employed.",
    "The academic performance of journals, nations/regions, academic institutions, and researchers was evaluated using bibliometric measures, including the Hirsch index (H-index) and average citations per article (ACP).",
    "The productivity and impact of actors were assessed according to the number of articles contributed and citations earned.",
    "The H-index was employed to assess contributors from both a standpoint of excellence and volume, while ACP was calculated by dividing the citation count by the article count."
